parameters: Zerachiel: Well, we are on a ship...

Zerachiel: It seems like we'll be
staying like this until we reach the
next continent.

Effy: Ugh... I wonder how much longer
until we arrive...?
Zerachiel and Effy are doing fine.

I think there are many difficulties
waiting ahead.

There may be tough times, and there may
be times when you cry.
I still think we'll manage somehow.

???: Well well, it seems like we're
enjoying peace.

????: With you right now, it seems like
it would be easy to take care of things.
Sariel: It's been a while, Zerachiel.

Sariel: You don't have to be so tense. I
just came here to say hello today.
Sariel: It seems like you didn't know.

Sariel: The Eden-sama you defeated was
just one of the four clones.

Sariel: Long ago, the gods started a
battle called the Final War, a fight
that determined the fate of the world.

Sariel: At that time, the former Giant
God King divided himself into four
clones in order to help the successor,
Eden-sama, and then perished.
Zerachiel: Well then, what about Eden...

Sariel: It means that there are still
three clones remaining.
Sariel: I'm going to revive Eden-sama.

Sariel: And this time, I will definitely
destroy the world.

Zerachiel: I won't let such a thing
happen!!

Sariel: Ahaha! Well then, why don't you
try to stop me?
Sariel: I'm heading towards the Empire.

Sariel: In the Empire, there once
existed a paradise of the gods.

Sariel: I'm pretty sure... Wasn't Aretia
a small island?

Sariel: That's where Eden-sama's soul is
sleeping.
Sariel: Well then, I'll go ahead.

Sariel: I hope the island remains until
you arrive!!
Effy: Let's head to Aretia as well.

Effy: I can't let Eden... be revived
again.

Zerachiel: I won't let Sariel have it
her way. ||||^

Zerachiel: In order to prevent any more
tragedies like this from happening...
||||^
Zerachiel: We'll crush your ambitions, once and for all!! ||||^
